==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Freemasonry]] - the intensive test to become a master mason.

In Freemasonry, at least historically, the [[wikipedia:Freemasonry#Principles and activities|modes of recognition]] & some other parts were never written down, & passed on only orally to the new Mason in three degrees. For each degree there are parts to be memorized by the new candidate, a test of said information given by the other brethren, and the next degree conferred with the extensive use of [[allegory]] (imagine a play, perhaps [[wikipedia:Shakespear|Shakespear]]). For each degree the memory work became much more extensive, & the plays longer & more dramatic. With the Third Degree, both the test and the allegory are so poignant that this termm came into existance.

